Detailed Description

Contains OO-like linked-list data structure for pairs.

This file contains an OO-like API for a linked list API of nitf_Pair objects (the first item is a string, the second is a generic pointer.

The structures are modeled on the C++ Standard Template Library.

NITF_BOOL nitf_List_insert ( nitf_List *  chain,
nitf_ListIterator  iter,
NITF_DATA *  data,
nitf_Error *  error 
)

Insert data into the chain BEFORE the iterator, and make the iterator point at the new node.


  1. If the iterator is pointing to NULL, we will insert into the back of this list
  2. If the iterator is pointing to the beginning, we will insert into the front

  3. If the iterator is pointing at something else, we will insert after the iterator (same case, in practice as pointing to the beginning)

Parameters:
chain The chain
iter The iterator to insert before
data This is a pointer assignment, not a data copy
error An error to populate on failure
Returns:
1 on success, 0 on failure
